<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-31T11:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/635.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Vice Consul at
                                    Foochow</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Foochow</hi></placeName>, ([<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1911-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1911-11-01T00:00:00+08:00">undated</date>;] <hi rend="italic">Received November 7, 1911.</hi>)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The right of asylum may be requested by the mandarins. Instructions
                            requested.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thompson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>